External anatomy. Flat base attached to substratum (rounded in one specimen), to 9 mm diameter. Column longer than wide, 19 mm long and 10 mm wide in preserved holotype ; mean of all observed specimens in preservation 19.3 mm long and 10.5 mm wide. Column divisible into physa, scapus, scapulus and capitulum ( Fig. 2 , 3 a). Cuticle covers scapus and scapulus ( Fig. 2 , 3 a, 3 b). Scapus brown, with tenaculi to which sand and gravel attach (
Fig. 2
). Scapulus lighter brown, without tenaculi or attached particles. Capitulum white, without tenaculi ( Fig. 2 , 3 a). When contracted, capitulum and scapulus covered by scapus.
